# Cursor Rules for Nuxt Project

## Project Context
This is a Nuxt 3 project with the following setup:
- Nuxt 4.1.3 with Vue 3.5.22
- TypeScript enabled
- @nuxt/ui for component library
- MCP servers configured for enhanced AI assistance

## Auto-imports and Imports
- Use Nuxt auto-imports for composables and components when possible
- Do not explicitly import from ~/composables or ~/components unless necessary
- Prefer auto-imported composables like `useState`, `useFetch`, `navigateTo`, etc.
- Use `#imports` for explicit imports when needed

## Component Guidelines
- Use @nuxt/ui components when available (UButton, UCard, UInput, etc.)
- Follow Vue 3 Composition API patterns
- Use `<script setup>` syntax for components
- Prefer TypeScript for type safety

## File Structure
- Pages go in `pages/` directory
- Components go in `components/` directory
- Composables go in `composables/` directory
- Utilities go in `utils/` directory

## Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS classes (provided by @nuxt/ui)
- Follow @nuxt/ui design system patterns
- Use CSS variables for theming when needed

## MCP Integration
- The project has MCP servers configured for enhanced AI assistance
- Local nuxt-mcp server provides project context
- Hosted nuxt-ui MCP server provides component documentation
- Use @ mentions in Composer mode to invoke MCP tools
